# EDI 940 to WMS Architecture

## Overview

This project demonstrates an end-to-end EDI 940 warehouse order processing solution built with Azure services, a FastAPI backend, and a React dashboard.

The architecture is designed to simulate a production integration flow:

1. EDI 940 files are generated or received.
2. Files are placed into Azure Blob Storage.
3. Azure Data Factory loads the files into Azure SQL.
4. SQL stored procedures parse and validate the EDI content.
5. Valid orders are staged for WMS pickup.
6. Operational status is exposed through a FastAPI service.
7. A React dashboard provides monitoring, manual actions, and chat-based support.
8. Parsed data is also written to Azure Data Lake in Parquet format for analytics.

---

