## Operational Flow

### File Intake

```text
Logic App or external sender
    ↓
Blob Storage
    ↓
File waits in edi940-inbound
```

### Batch Processing

```text
Dashboard Run Batch button
    ↓
FastAPI
    ↓
Azure Data Factory
    ↓
Read inbound files
    ↓
Insert into dbo.EDI940_Raw
```

### Parsing

```text
Raw EDI record
    ↓
ParseEDI940RawByFile
    ↓
Validate control segments and quantities
    ↓
Update status
```

### WMS Staging

```text
Parsed order
    ↓
OrderHeader_Staging
OrderDetail_Staging
    ↓
IntegrationStatus = READY
```

### WMS Pickup

```text
READY
    ↓
Simulated or real WMS pickup
    ↓
SUCCESS or FAILED
```

### Dashboard Monitoring

```text
React Dashboard
    ↓
FastAPI
    ↓
Azure SQL and Blob Storage
    ↓
Operational status cards and tables
```

---

## Design Principles

### Backend-Controlled AI

The model can select approved tools, but it cannot execute arbitrary SQL or access credentials.

### Parameterized SQL

User-supplied PO and ISA values are passed through parameterized queries.

### Separation of Concerns

- React handles presentation
- FastAPI handles API logic
- SQL handles parsing and persistence
- ADF handles orchestration
- Blob Storage handles file intake
- ADLS handles analytics storage
- Claude handles natural-language interpretation only

### Graceful Degradation

If Blob Storage, ADF, or the AI provider is unavailable, the API returns controlled error information rather than exposing secrets or crashing the entire dashboard.

### Operational Visibility

The system prioritizes visibility into:

- Backlog
- File age
- Parse failure
- WMS status
- Retry attempts
- Error messages

---

## Current Limitations

- AI rate limiting is stored in memory and is not globally shared across workers.
- SQL authentication still uses credentials rather than Managed Identity.
- ADF startup overhead is high for small files.
- The current WMS integration is simulated.
- The solution currently focuses on EDI 940.
- Some administrative actions still require stronger role-based authorization.
- Full idempotency and duplicate detection require additional hardening.
- Production alerting and automated remediation are not yet implemented.

---

